# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Secrets — NEVER commit. A leaked API key in a public repo
# stays in git history forever even if deleted later.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
.env
.env.local
*.key
*.pem

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Source data — PSX PDFs. Publish CODE, not DATA.
# These are the source regulatory documents (and large binaries).
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
*.pdf

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Working / handoff docs — local scaffolding, not portfolio.
# These reveal the build process; keep them off the public repo.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
PROJECT_CONTEXT.md
WRITEUP_STRUCTURE.md

# Note: the gold set (gold_set.json) and run logs (*_results.txt, full_run.txt)
# ARE published as evidence — they're derived from public regulatory disclosures,
# not PSX's restricted market-data feed. The source PDFs stay excluded above.

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Python
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
__pycache__/
*.py[cod]
*.egg-info/
.venv/
venv/
env/
.ipynb_checkpoints/

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# OS / editor cruft
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
.vscode/
.idea/
